<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6637&amp;p=65407#p65407"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Real NES like testing on an Emulator?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6637&amp;p=65407#p65407"><![CDATA[
Log the events and record the type (PC reached certain address, certain value written to certain register, etc.), along with a user-defined hex value. Then have something to represent the logged data in any medium, with filtering. So you could log all points on a timeline, or a 2D representation with 341 pixels per row, or as sound, etc. This way the event logging is completely independent of the representation when being examined.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Wed Aug 04, 2010 9:37 am</p><hr />
