<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6637&amp;p=64788#p64788"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Breakpoint, tintpoint, soundpoint, logpoint, savepoint, scriptpoint, cedarpoint, it's just an idea for making your debugger engine more <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthogonality#Computer_science" class="postlink">orthogonal</a>. It separates the "when" (e.g. opcode fetch, read address, write address, write particular data at address) from the "what" (stop execution, set the color, play a sound, write the registers and a bit of text, save a state for later analysis, run a Lua script, ride a roller coaster).<br /></div><br /><br />I see.  So in other words add a "Do this when hit..." to the Breakpoints dialog, where the list of things to do includes one (or more) of:<br /><br />Break<br />Mark<br />Save<br />Execute Lua script<br /><br />Makes a lot of sense, thanks!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3705">cpow</a> — Sat Jul 24, 2010 2:20 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
